title: Independent Candidate Sajid Khan wins NA-26 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Independent Candidate Sajid Khan has won the election for National Assembly constituency NA-26 Mohmand by securing 41,489 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Jamiat Ulema e Islam Pakistan Candidate Muhammad Arif, who bagged 19,930 votes.
Overall votersâ€™ turn-out remained 27.27 percent.
